## 9. SkyDexia 2.6
**What it does:**
- edits and manages workspace files
- records suite intents
- runs bounded controlled or autonomous workspace passes
- stages full-file operations and can auto-apply/save in autonomous mode
- issues packaged founder-unlock sessions and signed runtime tokens
- saves and reloads workspace snapshots through packaged server routes
- stores integration status and SkyeDrive restore-point records inside the package
- requires founder/session auth before packaged workspace, integration, SkyeDrive, and record reads are returned
- requires founder/session auth before packaged AI, mail, and SKNore preview routes can use provider credentials or server-side policy evaluation
- requires an explicitly configured session secret before packaged founder unlock can mint or verify runtime tokens
- seals connected GitHub and Netlify provider tokens inside the packaged runtime state
- only degrades to browser-local fallback when the packaged server lane is unavailable, instead of masking live auth or release failures with fake local success
- validates connected provider targets before persisting release-ready integration state when credentials are available
- previews SKNore release blocking before push/deploy actions
- routes packaged AI calls through 0megaSkyeGate only after founder/session auth is present
- routes packaged mail delivery through Resend only after founder/session auth is present
- executes packaged GitHub push and Netlify deploy actions against remote APIs when credentials are available
- records packaged GitHub push, Netlify deploy, and SkyeChat notification history
- materializes the saved workspace into a package-owned runtime directory
- starts, probes, logs, restarts, and stops local child processes through `/api/runtime/*`
- exposes runtime URLs from the same saved workspace state the package just materialized
- syncs workspace context into SovereignVariables
- reopens bridge drafts in SkyeBlog
- posts recalled records to SkyeChat
- sends recalled records to SkyeMail
- keeps save, sync, push, and deploy actions tied to the same workspace state

**Current user-facing function:**
- orchestration-heavy workspace editor with a packaged release/runtime lane that can really publish and locally own runtime/process execution without exposing anonymous provider-backed server actions

**Current connected behavior:**
- one of the strongest existing cross-app routing surfaces in the repo, now upgraded into the self-contained SkyDexia 2.6 package contract with packaged founder auth, gated workspace/integration/AI/mail/policy routes, SkyeDrive continuity, sealed provider credential storage, package-owned runtime/process control, secret-safe integration state, and real GitHub / Netlify release routes

---

